I don't even know yet...

277
00:17:18,850 --> 00:17:21,389
if I can really have a band.

278
00:17:22,785 --> 00:17:26,629
If you want to do it, I believe you can, son.

279
00:17:50,551 --> 00:17:52,273
Hey, Dad, Tim.

280
00:17:52,297 --> 00:17:54,421
I just finished cooking. Help yourselves.

281
00:17:59,054 --> 00:18:01,011
Hey Tim, and this...

282
00:18:01,011 --> 00:18:03,259
I made you a lunch box. Don't forget it.

283
00:18:05,002 --> 00:18:06,022
Wait.

284
00:18:07,497 --> 00:18:09,464
Don't we eat together first?

285
00:18:09,488 --> 00:18:10,969
I've already eaten.

286
00:18:10,994 --> 00:18:12,588
What time did you wake up, Win?

287
00:18:13,346 --> 00:18:15,926
Don't ask. Hurry up, or you'll be late for school.

288
00:18:28,041 --> 00:18:29,055
Tim.

289
00:18:29,291 --> 00:18:30,901
Use a fork and spoon, son.

290
00:18:31,926 --> 00:18:34,063
But it's okay. Never mind.

291
00:18:37,691 --> 00:18:39,164
Get some rice for me.

292
00:18:54,419 --> 00:18:55,638
Win.

293
00:19:02,268 --> 00:19:03,957
Here, I made this for you.

294
00:19:06,792 --> 00:19:08,125
Why did you make it for me?

295
00:19:09,467 --> 00:19:11,277
So you'll eat every meal.

296
00:19:11,301 --> 00:19:12,727
So you won't get dizzy again.

297
00:19:15,222 --> 00:19:16,455
Are you worried about me?

298
00:19:19,071 --> 00:19:21,399
I'm just afraid you won't be able to play the guitar.

299
00:19:21,933 --> 00:19:23,319
Here. I have to go now.

300
00:19:27,691 --> 00:19:28,724
See you later.

301
00:19:53,545 --> 00:19:55,841
What's with your mood?

302
00:19:57,321 --> 00:19:58,368
Biu.

303
00:19:58,454 --> 00:19:59,947
Are you free this evening?

304
00:20:00,881 --> 00:20:02,787
I'm not doing anything.

305
00:20:03,696 --> 00:20:05,631
Then let's go for a run.

306
00:20:07,372 --> 00:20:08,785
A run?

307
00:20:19,695 --> 00:20:20,882
Hurry up, you.

308
00:20:21,390 --> 00:20:23,063
Your legs are so damn short.

309
00:20:25,471 --> 00:20:27,433
Why do we have to run?

310
00:20:27,651 --> 00:20:28,799
You don't know?

311
00:20:28,824 --> 00:20:30,023
Do you know?

312
00:20:30,048 --> 00:20:32,837
Of course. To have a band and play a concert,

313
00:20:32,861 --> 00:20:34,602
we have to be strong, both physically...

314
00:20:34,948 --> 00:20:36,395
and mentally.

315
00:20:37,623 --> 00:20:39,711
But I'm the band manager.

316
00:20:42,330 --> 00:20:43,223
Oh, right.

317
00:20:43,616 --> 00:20:45,217
Why does she have to run with us?

318
00:20:45,388 --> 00:20:46,695
Shit.

319
00:20:48,609 --> 00:20:49,609
Come on.

320
00:20:50,158 --> 00:20:51,231
I can't anymore.

321
00:20:56,534 --> 00:20:57,701
My back hurts.

322
00:21:00,055 --> 00:21:00,922
Nut.

323
00:21:01,535 --> 00:21:03,028
Nut, Nut.

324
00:21:03,294 --> 00:21:04,076
Are you okay?
Nut.

325
00:21:12,561 --> 00:21:13,601
Are you okay?

326
00:21:20,841 --> 00:21:21,909
Perfectly fine.

327
00:21:24,881 --> 00:21:26,505
Fine, my ass.

328
00:21:26,940 --> 00:21:28,145
You don't have to run.

329
00:21:31,693 --> 00:21:32,913
You can just walk.

330
00:21:33,406 --> 00:21:34,526
Let's go.

331
00:21:37,353 --> 00:21:38,442
Slowly.

332
00:21:51,986 --> 00:21:53,059
Nut.

333
00:21:53,393 --> 00:21:55,113
It took a lot to get you here.

334
00:21:56,125 --> 00:21:57,480
Because I'm fine.

335
00:21:57,786 --> 00:21:59,547
You just made me run too much.

336
00:22:00,695 --> 00:22:02,583
Before you say you're fine,

337
00:22:02,829 --> 00:22:04,296
you should get a check-up to be sure.

338
00:22:09,733 --> 00:22:11,743
A check-up will wipe out my savings.

339
00:22:12,380 --> 00:22:13,747
Just use your health card.

340
00:22:15,413 --> 00:22:16,473
Health card?

341
00:22:17,244 --> 00:22:18,371
What health card?

342
00:22:24,869 --> 00:22:27,013
I meant your ATM card.

343
00:22:27,037 --> 00:22:28,604
Just use your ATM card.

344
00:22:30,616 --> 00:22:32,250
I'll go withdraw after the check-up.

345
00:22:37,976 --> 00:22:39,763
Nattanan, please.

346
00:22:46,287 --> 00:22:47,516
Why are you following me?

347
00:22:50,793 --> 00:22:53,546
I'm not. I'm just going to wait here.

348
00:22:58,641 --> 00:22:59,921
Nattanan.

349
00:22:59,946 --> 00:23:00,961
Last name?

350
00:23:00,961 --> 00:23:01,919
Tiwanit.

351
00:23:01,944 --> 00:23:02,946
This way, please.

352
00:23:04,752 --> 00:23:06,000
Hello, doctor.

353
00:23:32,934 --> 00:23:34,022
How did it go?

354
00:23:35,295 --> 00:23:36,788
The doctor said it's nothing.

355
00:23:37,610 --> 00:23:39,423
Just need to get enough rest, that's all.

356
00:23:40,999 --> 00:23:42,279
Are you sure?

357
00:23:45,089 --> 00:23:46,542
Why would I lie to you?

358
00:23:50,911 --> 00:23:53,514
Okay, I'm going to the ATM.

359
00:24:53,334 --> 00:24:54,394
Come here.

360
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:57,673
Who are you going to call?

361
00:24:57,920 --> 00:24:58,835
Call them.

362
00:24:58,860 --> 00:25:00,658
Come on, it's very easy.

363
00:25:00,682 --> 00:25:02,164
There's a button to press, right?

364
00:25:02,189 --> 00:25:04,071
Press it, wait for someone,

365
00:25:04,095 --> 00:25:06,026
and then talk. Very easy.

366
00:25:09,851 --> 00:25:11,483
Okay, you can do it.

367
00:25:31,409 --> 00:25:32,536
Hello.

368
00:25:34,375 --> 00:25:35,602
Hello.

369
00:25:36,142 --> 00:25:38,783
May I speak to Nut, please?

370
00:25:39,396 --> 00:25:40,383
Who's calling?

371
00:25:41,998 --> 00:25:44,973
My name is Win. I'm a friend of Nut's.

372
00:25:47,247 --> 00:25:49,313
Nut, Win calling you.

373
00:25:59,124 --> 00:26:00,144
What's up?

374
00:26:01,998 --> 00:26:06,173
Hey, are you going to bed yet?

375
00:26:06,492 --> 00:26:07,699
Almost.

376
00:26:08,321 --> 00:26:09,975
You need to sleep early, you know?

377
00:26:09,999 --> 00:26:11,580
Just as the doctor ordered.

378
00:26:12,086 --> 00:26:13,100
Yeah.

379
00:26:14,786 --> 00:26:16,052
Then...

380
00:26:17,365 --> 00:26:18,365
That's all.

381
00:26:19,633 --> 00:26:21,126
You called just for that?

382
00:26:21,993 --> 00:26:25,279
Or is there something else you want to talk?

383
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:30,279
Oh, your lunch box is with me.

384
00:26:30,973 --> 00:26:32,779
I'll wash it and give it back to you.

385
00:26:34,725 --> 00:26:35,902
And also...

386
00:26:36,888 --> 00:26:38,519
You don't have to make it anymore.

387
00:26:39,083 --> 00:26:40,503
I can find my own food.

388
00:26:41,578 --> 00:26:44,444
Oh, was it not delicious?

389
00:26:45,397 --> 00:26:46,491
No.

390
00:26:47,202 --> 00:26:48,322
It's just that...

391
00:26:48,682 --> 00:26:50,188
I feel bad for troubling you.

392
00:26:52,255 --> 00:26:54,103
You don't have to feel bad.

393
00:26:54,536 --> 00:26:55,586
Because...

394
00:26:55,611 --> 00:26:58,012
you like to eat all sorts of weird things.

395
00:26:58,036 --> 00:26:59,466
You might faint again.

396
00:26:59,491 --> 00:27:01,418
It's better if I make it for you.

397
00:27:04,091 --> 00:27:05,413
You're so stubborn.

398
00:27:07,251 --> 00:27:08,114
Well,

399
00:27:08,291 --> 00:27:10,089
It's enough that I'm the only stubborn one.

400
00:27:10,149 --> 00:27:11,736
You're not allowed to be stubborn.

401
00:27:13,191 --> 00:27:14,667
See you tomorrow.

402
00:27:16,931 --> 00:27:18,033
Good night.

403
00:27:19,835 --> 00:27:21,055
Good night.

404
00:27:48,662 --> 00:27:49,895
Let's trade.

405
00:27:50,579 --> 00:27:52,227
Let me make for you.

406
00:27:59,368 --> 00:28:00,501
Let's trade.

407
00:28:01,651 --> 00:28:03,449
How many lunch boxes do you have at home?

408
00:28:06,838 --> 00:28:08,058
So,

409
00:28:08,891 --> 00:28:10,293
what did you make for me?

410
00:28:11,891 --> 00:28:14,681
I'm not telling. It's a surprise.

411
00:28:27,152 --> 00:28:29,619
Look at you.

412
00:28:29,765 --> 00:28:31,777
Morning, you don't come to school together.

413
00:28:32,413 --> 00:28:35,555
At lunch, you bring a lunch box to eat alone.

414
00:28:36,610 --> 00:28:38,203
I feel so left out.

415
00:28:41,142 --> 00:28:42,911
What are you feeling left out about?

416
00:28:44,971 --> 00:28:46,778
Wow, look at that. So much food.

417
00:28:48,611 --> 00:28:50,683
Then I'll eat it.

418
00:28:50,710 --> 00:28:51,857
Mm.

419
00:28:56,724 --> 00:28:57,771
What's wrong?

420
00:28:58,736 --> 00:29:00,589
Did you make this yourself?

421
00:29:01,567 --> 00:29:02,622
No.

422
00:29:06,251 --> 00:29:07,611
Which shop did you buy this from?

423
00:29:07,635 --> 00:29:10,408
You should report them to the police. It's so salty.

424
00:29:21,414 --> 00:29:23,414
You eat it all by yourself. I'm done.

425
00:29:41,281 --> 00:29:42,281
Hey.

426
00:29:43,089 --> 00:29:45,028
My dad and mom gave me permission.

427
00:29:45,882 --> 00:29:47,135
I'll join the band with you.

428
00:29:49,130 --> 00:29:50,163
Really?

429
00:29:50,972 --> 00:29:53,348
The competition we're entering is Star of Band.

430
00:29:53,373 --> 00:29:55,943
Simple rule: all songs must be original compositions.

431
00:29:56,017 --> 00:29:57,594
The first round is a video submission.

432
00:29:57,618 --> 00:29:59,280
Anyway, I'm counting on you to film it, Biu.

433
00:29:59,347 --> 00:30:00,133
Got it.

434
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:02,228
So what song are we using for the competition?

435
00:30:02,253 --> 00:30:04,172
Right now, we have a song that Nut wrote.

436
00:30:04,196 --> 00:30:05,684
We just need to practice until we're in sync.

437
00:30:15,134 --> 00:30:17,522
Ek, I think it's...

438
00:30:17,604 --> 00:30:19,328
it doesn't really fit the song.

439
00:30:20,381 --> 00:30:21,541
I'm sorry.

440
00:30:22,240 --> 00:30:24,827
Hey, it's his first day.

441
00:30:26,279 --> 00:30:27,509
It's okay.

442
00:30:27,533 --> 00:30:28,994
There's still time.

443
00:30:29,234 --> 00:30:30,642
There's no time left.

444
00:30:31,141 --> 00:30:33,362
They're closing applications in a few days.

445
00:30:36,965 --> 00:30:38,651
Let's try it one more time.

446
00:30:55,436 --> 00:30:56,623
I think...

447
00:30:57,062 --> 00:30:58,416
you should slow it down a bit.

448
00:30:58,857 --> 00:31:01,350
Just follow my lead.

449
00:31:02,070 --> 00:31:03,172
I think you can do it.

450
00:31:04,465 --> 00:31:05,378
Come on.

451
00:31:05,951 --> 00:31:07,099
One more time.

452
00:31:10,701 --> 00:31:11,747
Go.

453
00:31:15,925 --> 00:31:19,654
♪ From now on, I will love you ♪

454
00:31:19,678 --> 00:31:23,409
♪ Like it's the last time I'll ever see you. ♪

455
00:31:23,433 --> 00:31:27,165
♪ I won't go anywhere, I will stay by your side ♪

456
00:31:27,190 --> 00:31:30,775
♪ To make you feel good. ♪

457
00:31:30,799 --> 00:31:34,739
♪ There will be me, there will be us. ♪

458
00:31:34,764 --> 00:31:38,874
♪ Every day will be like this. ♪

459
00:31:38,899 --> 00:31:45,510
♪ I will love you forever. ♪

460
00:31:50,147 --> 00:31:51,961
That's better.

461
00:31:56,418 --> 00:31:57,878
The recording great, right?

462
00:32:08,633 --> 00:32:10,300
I'm so tired today.

463
00:32:14,461 --> 00:32:15,867
Thank you.

464
00:32:17,082 --> 00:32:18,118
No problem.

465
00:32:18,491 --> 00:32:20,181
Actually, you can play well.

466
00:32:20,383 --> 00:32:21,638
Just be more confident.

467
00:32:22,011 --> 00:32:23,105
Okay.

468
00:32:23,412 --> 00:32:24,506
How are you getting home?

469
00:32:24,972 --> 00:32:26,161
Want me to give you a ride?

470
00:32:26,935 --> 00:32:28,068
It's okay.

471
00:32:28,754 --> 00:32:30,281
My driver is already here.

472
00:32:33,433 --> 00:32:34,424
Hi.

473
00:32:35,053 --> 00:32:36,033
Let's go.

474
00:32:36,236 --> 00:32:37,450
See you tomorrow.

475
00:32:40,486 --> 00:32:41,726
This way, master.

476
00:33:49,911 --> 00:33:51,184
Mom.

477
00:33:52,330 --> 00:33:53,463
Mom.

478
00:33:56,733 --> 00:33:58,013
Mom.

479
00:33:59,318 --> 00:34:01,425
Mom, can you hear me?

480
00:34:04,484 --> 00:34:06,719
Mom, Mom.

481
00:34:58,168 --> 00:34:59,421
Are you okay?

482
00:35:03,993 --> 00:35:04,913
This is...

483
00:35:06,450 --> 00:35:07,723
the reason why...

484
00:35:09,734 --> 00:35:11,506
I don't want anyone buying liquor for her.

485
00:35:14,856 --> 00:35:16,023
I'm sorry.

486
00:35:24,689 --> 00:35:25,982
It's good that you guys came.

487
00:35:27,974 --> 00:35:29,374
Can you watch my mom for a bit?

488
00:35:31,746 --> 00:35:32,926
I'm going to get something to eat.

489
00:36:33,536 --> 00:36:34,709
Chai.

490
00:36:37,143 --> 00:36:38,377
You scared me.

491
00:36:39,005 --> 00:36:40,112
How did you get here?

492
00:36:45,099 --> 00:36:47,602
My parents brought me for health check-up.

493
00:36:48,100 --> 00:36:50,588
Win told me your mom wasn't feeling well.

494
00:36:50,941 --> 00:36:52,168
Is she okay?

495
00:36:53,221 --> 00:36:55,369
She's fine now.

496
00:36:55,996 --> 00:36:58,099
She'll likely be discharged after one more night.

497
00:36:59,499 --> 00:37:00,606
That's great.

498
00:37:04,622 --> 00:37:05,669
I'm hungry.

499
00:37:06,837 --> 00:37:08,143
I'm going to get something to eat.

500
00:38:36,603 --> 00:38:37,737
Excuse me.

501
00:38:38,132 --> 00:38:39,372
Hello.

502
00:38:39,872 --> 00:38:41,440
This medical bill...

503
00:38:42,562 --> 00:38:44,311
can I pay it in installments?

504
00:38:47,346 --> 00:38:48,541
For this amount,

505
00:38:48,565 --> 00:38:50,674
it looks like it was just paid a moment ago.

506
00:38:51,896 --> 00:38:53,127
It's been paid?

507
00:38:53,152 --> 00:38:54,049
Yes.

508
00:38:55,208 --> 00:38:56,188
Who paid it?

509
00:38:56,213 --> 00:38:57,871
It was a man and a woman.

510
00:38:57,895 --> 00:38:59,763
They just walked that way a moment ago.

511
00:39:04,941 --> 00:39:05,999
Thank you.

512
00:39:12,372 --> 00:39:13,732
Sir, Ma'am.

513
00:39:15,247 --> 00:39:16,914
Are you the ones who...

514
00:39:17,246 --> 00:39:19,239
paid for my mother's medical bill?

515
00:39:21,851 --> 00:39:22,912
Yes, we are.

516
00:39:25,940 --> 00:39:27,586
Thank you so much.

517
00:39:29,720 --> 00:39:30,628
Somehow,

518
00:39:31,580 --> 00:39:33,126
I will find a way to pay you back soon.

519
00:39:34,263 --> 00:39:35,811
It's really no problem.

520
00:39:35,835 --> 00:39:38,051
Don't rush to pay us back.

521
00:39:38,344 --> 00:39:40,407
Ek told me that...

522
00:39:40,432 --> 00:39:43,053
Chai takes very good care of him.

523
00:39:43,860 --> 00:39:47,561
So, consider this a payment for you taking care of Ek.

524
00:39:47,586 --> 00:39:48,635
Okay?

525
00:39:50,525 --> 00:39:51,865
I can't do that, ma'am.

526
00:39:53,131 --> 00:39:54,586
Taking care of him is one thing.

527
00:39:55,350 --> 00:39:58,192
But I'll still find a way to pay you back.

528
00:40:00,024 --> 00:40:01,820
In that case, you and your band...

529
00:40:01,845 --> 00:40:04,096
can help me with an event instead, how about that?

530
00:40:04,201 --> 00:40:06,196
That's a good idea. I agree.

531
00:40:07,529 --> 00:40:08,617
Yes, of course.

532
00:40:09,360 --> 00:40:10,736
Any kind of event is fine.

533
00:40:18,447 --> 00:40:20,598
I think this event has a good crowd.

534
00:40:20,905 --> 00:40:22,333
So when we go out to play,

535
00:40:22,357 --> 00:40:24,264
You can find a good angle around there.

536
00:40:24,384 --> 00:40:25,968
And use this one, okay?

537
00:40:25,993 --> 00:40:27,108
- Okay.
- Is the camera ready?

538
00:40:27,132 --> 00:40:28,169
It's fully charged.

539
00:40:34,353 --> 00:40:36,166
How is it? Are you ready?

540
00:40:37,412 --> 00:40:38,794
Does this really suit me?

541
00:40:39,848 --> 00:40:41,194
You look very handsome, Chai.

542
00:40:41,659 --> 00:40:43,115
If you don't believe me, ask Ek.

543
00:40:44,301 --> 00:40:45,428
Is it true, Ek?

544
00:40:50,984 --> 00:40:52,090
It's almost good.

545
00:40:52,563 --> 00:40:54,610
See? "Almost good"...

546
00:40:55,150 --> 00:40:56,623
doesn't mean it's good.

547
00:41:14,931 --> 00:41:16,290
Now it's good.

548
00:41:24,051 --> 00:41:25,337
Anyway,

549
00:41:25,361 --> 00:41:27,702
thanks a lot for coming to help.

550
00:41:28,653 --> 00:41:30,089
It'd be strange if I didn't come.

551
00:41:30,113 --> 00:41:31,481
I was the one who caused it.

552
00:41:32,372 --> 00:41:34,811
I think you should thank Nut instead.

553
00:41:35,070 --> 00:41:36,442
He has nothing to do with it.

554
00:41:38,403 --> 00:41:39,517
Consider it...

555
00:41:40,171 --> 00:41:42,315
a repayment for the your breakfast.

556
00:41:46,757 --> 00:41:47,842
Hey guys,

557
00:41:48,582 --> 00:41:50,006
this band is almost done.

558
00:41:50,030 --> 00:41:51,595
It's almost our turn.

559
00:41:54,809 --> 00:41:55,855
